[{"location":"index.html#Custom-ARIMA-Forecasting-with-Airline-Passengers-Dataset","page":"Home","title":"Custom ARIMA Forecasting with Airline Passengers Dataset","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html#Introduction","page":"Home","title":"Introduction","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"This tutorial demonstrates how to use CustomARIMA in Julia to fit an ARIMA model and forecast future values using the airline passengers dataset.","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#Prerequisites","page":"Home","title":"Prerequisites","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Ensure you have the following Julia packages installed:","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.add([\"CSV\", \"DataFrames\", \"CustomARIMA\"])","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#Loading-the-Dataset","page":"Home","title":"Loading the Dataset","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"The airline passengers dataset contains monthly totals of airline passengers from 1949 to 1960. First, load the dataset using CSV.jl and DataFrames.jl:","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"using CSV, DataFrames, CustomARIMA\n\nairpass = CSV.read(\"airline_passengers.csv\", DataFrame)\ny = airpass.Passengers","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Example Output:","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":" Month    Passengers\n 1949-01  112\n 1949-02  118\n 1949-03  132\n 1949-04  129\n 1949-05  121\n 1949-06  135\n 1949-07  148\n 1949-08  148\n 1949-09  136\n 1949-10  119\n 1949-11  104\n 1949-12  118\n 1950-01  115\n 1950-02  126\n 1950-03  141","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#Fitting-an-ARIMA-Model","page":"Home","title":"Fitting an ARIMA Model","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"We fit an ARIMA(2,1,1) model to the data:","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"model = CustomARIMA.arima(y, 2, 1, 1)\n\n# Print model details\nprintln(\"AR coefficients: \", model.ar_coef)\nprintln(\"MA coefficients: \", model.ma_coef)\nprintln(\"Residual variance: \", model.sigma2)","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Output:","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"AR coefficients: [1.0948936024577118, -0.497156521361955]\nMA coefficients: [-0.845931080745734]\nResidual variance: 844.3485015557588","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#Forecasting-Future-Values","page":"Home","title":"Forecasting Future Values","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"We generate 12-step-ahead forecasts using our fitted model:","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"forecasts = CustomARIMA.forecast(model, 12)\nprintln(\"Forecasts: \", forecasts)","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Forecast Output:","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"[471.92, 491.08, 492.22, 483.94, 474.30, 467.87, 465.62, 466.35, 468.27, 470.01, 470.96, 471.14]","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#Preparing-Data-for-Plotting","page":"Home","title":"Preparing Data for Plotting","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"To visualize the actual and forecasted values, structure the data as follows:","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Y_df = DataFrame(ds=collect(1:length(y)), Passengers=y)\nY_hat_df = DataFrame(ds=collect(length(y)+1:length(y)+12), Passengers=forecasts)","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#Plotting-the-Results","page":"Home","title":"Plotting the Results","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Finally, plot the original series and forecasts using CustomARIMA.plot_series:","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CustomARIMA.plot_series(Y_df, Y_hat_df)","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"This will generate a plot showing the actual airline passenger counts along with the 12-month forecast.","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#Conclusion","page":"Home","title":"Conclusion","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"This tutorial covered:","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Loading time series data in Julia\nFitting an ARIMA(2,1,1) model\nGenerating 12-step-ahead forecasts\nVisualizing results","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"(Image: Forecast Plot)","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"You can experiment with different ARIMA parameters (p,d,q) to improve the model's accuracy.","category":"page"}]
